{
  "texts": [
    "Appendix B.3 breaks down the composition of AI-related job tasks by occupation and task category, and provides example tasks for each pair.",
    "Notably, most new work revolves around integrating and overseeing the use of AI chatbots.",
    "Specifically, only 41% of new tasks focus on \"productive AI use\" (AI Ideation, AI Content Drafting, and AI Data Insights), while the remaining 59% relate to \"AI implementation and oversight\" (AI Quality Review, AI Integration, and AI Ethics & Compliance).",
    "35 workplaces that merely encourage chatbot use have a higher share of \"productive AI tasks\" focused on content generation and ideation.",
    "Consistent with the finding that AI chatbot workloads extend beyond direct use, 35 The most common task relates to the integration of AI chatbots into the workplace, accounting for 15%-40% of all new tasks, with the highest shares observed in IT support and software development."
  ]
}